description: Bachata & Merengue are both dances from the Dominican Republic. dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

event_name: Texture Your Moves for West Coast Swing
description: We will guide you through practical musicality and movement drills that will 'colour in' any pattern in your repertoire. You'll learn how to do more styling without feeling inhibited or being reckless, preserve your partnership connection while still expressing yourself, enjoy being musical even with partners who are missing skills, and respect the rules of the WCS while learning to bend them. Come learn a super practical & universal way to LEVEL UP your musicality by adding body pulse & groove to add more personality and creativity into basic patterns, then get lots of reps to practice these tactics with the appropriate connection and timing. All the while putting these skills to use immediately in your social dancing! In this workshop we are going to take your Feetwork, Bodywork and Grooves you might ALREADY know.. with your common WCS patterns. We will show you ways to texture a Tandem Slingshot, Hustle Check, Over Rotated Under Arm Turn. Leg Sweep to a Lunge. This workshop is for you if; You have no idea how to dance differently to different genres of music, so most of your dances look or feel the same. You feel like you are just walking through patterns without any real character to your movement and you feel robotic and stiff. You can do body pulse and contra-body but they are not automatic in your dancing yet. You can't seem to make wise, deliberate choices for texturing your moves to the music. You aren‚Äôt able to make your slow tempo songs look distinct from your other genres. **Send e-transfer to reserve your spot to danceyourfreedom@gmail.com Call Jay @ (250) 886-4599 if you have any questions. Please bring shoes or socks & your own water bottle. Space is limited to 14ppl max. You do NOT need a partner!
location: 516 Quadra ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8V3S3, CA
price: $30 via etransfer (for 2hr workshop) $40 (if paying at the door)

description: Bachata & Merengue are both dances from the Dominican Republic. dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

description:
We are excited to bring you dancing the 2nd Saturday of every month right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 8:15pm Doors open
Salsa Caliente‚Äôs team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson
Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:30pm- midnight
Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite. There will be a small non-alcoholic concession available as a fundraiser for the teams. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: STUDIO 4 ATHLETICS, 715 YATES ST, , BC, V8W 1L6, CA
